HEADWORD: Marguerite
<hw>Mar"gue*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a pearl, a
daisy. See <er>Margarite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The daisy
(<spn>Bellis perennis</spn>). The name is often applied also to the
ox-eye daisy and to the China aster.</def>
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

